  "original_title": "\u0b8e\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bca\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b9a\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bc7\u0bb2\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b87\u0bb0\u0bc1 \u0bae\u0bb0\u0ba3\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Two more deaths in fuel row",
      "author": "T. Saranya",
      "body_lines": [
        "(M.Y.M.Siam) Two people have died while waiting in line to get fuel in two different parts of the country. The police said that they died yesterday (22). A person who was waiting in line to get fuel at the Mathugamamatthugama Belawatta petrol station died after suddenly recovering and being admitted to Meekahathenna Hospital. The deceased is a 70-year-old man from Vallallvita area. He was waiting in line to get fuel for his motorbikes at the Kinniathirukonamalai-Kinnia IOC filling station and died after being admitted to the hospital due to a sudden illness. Died. The deceased is a 59-year-old man. The police have conducted further investigations into the incident."
      ],
